						<summary>

						<p>On the second pillar in the <hi rend="italic">maṇḍapa</hi> in front of the Rāmanātha shrine in the Vēdāraṇyēśvara temple.</p>						

						<p>This inscription in Sanskrit verse engraved in Grantha characters of about the 10th century records the gift of 90 sheep for a lamp to lord Śiva by Kalikēsarin. (See No. 524 below).</p>						

